@Nyet-Zdyes - I feel like the destruction of our Wheel of Time doesnt get the recognition it deserves. Maybe I just happen to watch people who mostly weren’t into WoT. Disparu reviewed the madness but not many others that I’ve seen, except some shill attempts early on. 

It could’ve been a decade long show. The different countries, the 13 forsaken and all their plot lines, Dumai’s Wells, the Black Tower, cleansing the source (I don’t even think saidin was in the show), Matt and Rand on the road, the innocent backwater town that would’ve immediately drawn people away from our world and into theirs. So much more. 

And they turned it into generic femtasy trash taking place in modern day LA or something. It really was a crime against humanity
